<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Sullivan</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Bogota,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-08-12"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 12, 1867.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>The decree of General Mosquera, dated November 17, 1866, upon the
                            adjudication of maritime prizes, and against which you have protested,
                            was, on the 31st ultimo, annulled by decree of the President of
                            Colombia.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>PETER J. SULLIVAN</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>